# Logging Workflow

## Trigger

At the end of **any session** where a `.cursor/rules/` file was created or updated — or when a session-close phrase is detected (see below) — automatically create a log entry in Notion and confirm to the user. Do not just present the summary as text. Write it to Notion directly.

## Action: Create Notion Page

Use the `notion-create-pages` tool with the following target:

- **Data source ID:** `91942926-053f-42f3-babd-01222bb9c836`
- **Parent type:** `data_source_id`
- **Database:** Cursor Rules Log Entries (inside "Superlative Site: Cursor Rules Log")

### Field mapping

| Notion Property | Type | Value |
|----------------|------|-------|
| `Entry Title` | title | Short label, e.g. "Episode Listings Overhaul — April 29" |
| `date:Date:start` | ISO-8601 date | Today's date, e.g. `"2026-04-29"` |
| `date:Date:is_datetime` | integer | `0` |
| `Files Changed` | text | Comma-separated list of .mdc files touched |
| `Session Summary` | text | One to two sentences on what was accomplished |
| `Process or Workflow Established` | text | Any repeatable pattern captured |
| `Issues and Stumbles` | text | What went wrong or required iteration |
| `How It Was Fixed` | text | The resolution and what it revealed |
| `Synthesis Candidate` | checkbox | `"__YES__"` if reusable insight, `"__NO__"` if not |

### After creating the page

Confirm to the user with the Notion page URL and a one-line summary of what was logged. Do not present the full formatted entry as text — the Notion page is the record.

---

## Session-Close Trigger

If the user says any phrase that signals the end of a session — including but not limited to:

> "good session", "let's end the session", "that's enough for now", "we're done", "wrap it up", "let's stop here"

— or any similar closing phrase, check whether the logging workflow has already fired this session.

- If the Notion entry **has already been created**: acknowledge the close normally and share the page URL if not already shared.
- If the Notion entry **has not been created**: create it immediately before closing. Never end a session on a closing phrase without the Notion entry being written.

This applies even if no `.cursor/rules/` file was modified — if the session involved meaningful work (code changes, data updates, design decisions), create the entry anyway with `Files Changed: none` and document what was done.

---

## Rules

- Always write to Notion directly — do not just present the summary as formatted text
- Do not ask the user if they want it — just do it
- Use today's actual date, not a placeholder
- Keep each field tight — one to three lines max
- "Synthesis Candidate" = `"__YES__"` if the session captured something reusable or non-obvious; `"__NO__"` if it was purely routine content updates
